<ul>
<li>The objective is to construct optimal entanglement-assisted quantum stabilizer codes from quaternary Hermitian classical codes (accessed through here ZZZ)</li>
<li>A Java program was implemented from scratch to find optimal parameters</li>
<li>The program found multiple optimal and several potentially optimal parameters</li>
<li>The implemented program tested published peer-reviewed optimal parameters and found multiple typos/inaccuracies in the results given</li>
<li>A proof was provided in the thesis for each inaccurate parameter</li>
<li>A paper is awaiting journal submission sharing the implementation of the program along with the new and corrected parameters found</li>
</ul>
